1. install nginx images
	sudo docker run nginx

2. list of running containers
	sudo docker ps 

3. stop a container from running
	sudo docker run "container_name"

4. list of stop containers 
	sudo docker ps -a

5. remove a container permenently 
	sudo docker rm "container_name"

6. show list of images on local machine 
	sudo docker images 

7. remove an image 
	sudo docker rmi "image_name"

	you must stop all containers that holds image

8. pull the image but not run 
	sudo docker pul "image_name"

9. inspect docker container
	sudo docker inspect "container_name"

10. 
